'''Jett Lucas''' (born [[February 17]],<ref name="Twitter" /> [[1993]])<ref name="This Week! Ep2" /> is the adopted son of [[George Lucas]]. He has cameos in both [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']] as a young [[Jedi]] [[Padawan]] named [[Zett Jukassa]]. As a young boy, Jett inspired the name of the [[Gungan]] species.<ref name="RollingStone">{{WebCite|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-news/jar-jar-binks-a-digital-star-is-born-50301|text=Jar Jar Binks: A Digital Star Is Born|author=Dunn, Jancee|date=1999-06-24|work=Rolling Stone|archivedate=20200509122715}}</ref> Jett is credited as an intern in the video game ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed]]''. In the ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' television series, the character [[Ion Papanoida]] is based on him.

Jett Lucas has been credited as a visual effects production assistant in ''[[Star Wars: The Mandalorian]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: The Book of Boba Fett]]''.

